  legend
    # = Solid color 0x68
    B = Breakable color 0x67
    . = Empty color 0x0E
    l = Line color 0x0E
    N = Normal color 0x66
    S = Solid color 0x6E
    ~ = Water color 0x1B
    o = Object color 0x1E
    k = Key color 0x0E
    @ = Player color 0x1F under Empty color 0x0E
    a = Empty color 0x08
    O = Object color 0x0F
  end

  stats
    stat at 43,6 element Object p1 cp437:0x0F p2 4 step north under Solid color 0x6E
    oop
@steamboard
#end
:touch
#play tc+e+g
Steam schematics, half-legible. It reads:
The trap valve seals the vault stair
below.
Shut down the boilers, then the way opens.
The brass key waits in the steam chamber.
#end
    end
    stat at 44,6 element Object cycle 0 p1 cp437:0x9D p2 4 step north under Solid color 0x6E
    oop
@boilergauge
#end
:touch
#play tc
Pressure gauge: needle pinned in the red.
#end
    end
    stat at 25,22 element Object cycle 2 p1 cp437:0x9D p2 4 step north under Breakable color 0x67
    oop
@brasskey2
#end
:touch
#play tcdefgab
A brass key, warm to the touch. Number
two.
#give brownkey
The steam chamber falls silent.
#die
    end
    stat at 45,6 element Object p1 cp437:0x0F p2 4 step north under Breakable color 0x67
    oop
@trapvalve
#end
:touch
#lock
#play tf-f-f
The steam trap valve hisses under your
hand.
#if brownkey no
#play cegceg
The valve turns. The vault stair unseals!
#unlock
#end
:no
#play f-c-f-c
